Nigeria Screens World Bank Chief for Cabinet Post, Vanguard Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-07-05T07:50:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-05/nigeria-screens-world-bank-chief-for-cabinet-post-vanguard-says.html
Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala, a managing
director at the  World Bank , will appear before Nigeria’s Senate
today to be screened for a cabinet position,  Vanguard  reported,
citing an unidentified security official.  Okonjo-Iweala, a former finance minister of the country,
was given security clearance by police yesterday, the Lagos-
based newspaper said. She is expected to return to her previous
post with additional powers to oversee the country’s economic
management, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
